  "texts": [
    "Pao et al. [76] proposed that the green element of a retina image was utilized to compute the entropy image.",
    "They trained this network on the publicly accessible Kaggle dataset that used a high-end graphics processing unit (GPU), and showed outstanding results, especially for a high-level classification problem.",
    "Figure 4.1 gives us the sample of a severe non-proliferative DR (NPDR) fundus image that shows the severity and likelihood, of the presence of microaneurysm, hemorrhage, and exudate.",
    "Figure 4.2 outlines the general measures taken by a CNN model to categorize fundus images into 5 severity categories.",
    "Table 4.2 presents the summary of research works corresponding to DR diagnosis using CNN."
  ]
}